The Forsaken Temple of Gildila the Demonic 07

Level 7

General
HistoryThe dungeon was created by hobgoblins as a mine. Its creators were destroyed by a natural disaster, and the dungeon has lain empty for many years until recently.
SizeMedium (51 x 51)
WallsHewn Stone (DC 20 to climb)
FloorNatural Stone (difficult terrain, disadvantage on acrobatics)
TemperatureWarm
IlluminationDark (individual creatures may carry lights)
Corridor Features
aA toppled statue lies across the corridor
cA shallow pool of acid covers the floor
eCobwebs fill the corridor
iA narrow shaft descends from the corridor into a plundered tomb below
mA tile labyrinth covers the floor
nA mouldy odor fills the corridor
rA putrid odor fills the corridor
sTeleporter Crystal: DC 15 to find, DC 15 to disable; affects each creature which touches the crystal, DC 11 save or be teleported to another location
uA 15-foot wide chasm cuts across the corridor
vRune of Fear: DC 15 to find, DC 10 to disable; affects all targets within 10 ft., DC 10 save or become frightened for 1d4 rounds
Wandering Monsters
15 x Gibbering Mouther (cr 2, mm 157); hard, 2250 xp; patrolling their territory
27 x Giant Spider (cr 1, mm 328); medium, 1400 xp; bloodied and fleeing a more powerful enemy
32 x Chimera (cr 6, mm 39); deadly, 4600 xp; consumed by disease and madness
44 x Yuan-ti Malison (cr 3, mm 309); hard, 2800 xp; scouting from another part of the dungeon
511 x Yuan-ti Pureblood (cr 1, mm 310); hard, 2200 xp; hunting for food
6Bulette (cr 5, mm 34); easy, 1800 xp; wielding bizarre eldritch powers
